Zamfara State Governor, Abdulaziz Yari is currently meeting with the Vice President, Professor Yemi Osinbajo at the State House Villa, Abuja, Daily Trust online reports. The Governor who arrived by 2.04pm went straight into the Vice President office at the State House Villa, Abuja for the meeting. Our correspondent reports that the closed doors meeting was still on as at the time this story was filed. Yari is one of the three governors who had issues with the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole over the just concluded party primaries. Ibikunle Amosun of Ogun state and Rocahas Okorocha of Imo state are the two other governors who have issues with Oshiomhole. Osinbajo, NGF chair meet over bailout Osinbajo, NGF chair meet over bailout Update: El-Rufai, Shettima join Yari's meeting with Osinbajo